dignus es cum tua religione, odium. This is the reading of A C P, and it was accepted by Donatus: other MSS. read odio. nodum in scirpo quaeris, lit. ‘ you are looking for a knot in a bulrush,' i. e. you are trying to find a difficulty where there is none. The proverb is also found in Pl. Men. 2. 1. 22, Ennius ap. Fest.
